VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT \b(memset|mlock|setrlimit|unlink|remove|std::string)\s*\(
WHEN EXPR MISSING:memset\s*\(|SecureZeroMemory|explicit_bzero|sodium_memzero|encrypt|cipher|redact && MISSING:test|example
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects the improper handling of sensitive data.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Insecure Handling of Sensitive Data.
